The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 The City Diary

 Robin Shaw, a 30-year-old security guard at a multi-storeyed building in Chitpur, died after being electrocuted on Sunday morning. The mishap occurred while Shaw was repairing a water pump at Basundhara Apartment in Uma Kanta Shaw Lane, where he used to work. He was taken to RG Kar Medical College and Hospital, where doctors pronounced him dead.

 Members of the Howrah district Chhatra Parishad on Sunday burnt the effigy of higher education minister Satyasadhan Chakraborty and blocked GT Road to protest police action on the agitating students of Jadavpur University. Around 200 Chhatra Parishad activists gathered on the Howrah Maidan and burnt the minister?s effigy. The blockade continued for 45 minutes, till police dispersed the protesters. District Chhatra Parishad president Shyamal Mitra alleged that around 40 protesters were arrested. They were released on personal risk bond. 

 Three dacoits were arrested in Howrah on Sunday. Police said Habul, 46, Uttam, 26, and Seikh Bapi, 22, were arrested while they were plotting a dacoity near a closed factory in Shibpur. A revolver and a bullet were seized from Habul, against whom two warrants were pending.

 The Federation of Association of Cottage and Small Industries on Saturday discussed the presentation made by the Indo-German Chamber of Commerce on ?Senior German Technical Experts Services?. The meet also discussed the implications of VAT and had an audio-visual presentation on insurance. 

 Traffic sergeant Soumen Dutta was injured after being knocked down by a long-distance state bus at the crossing of MG Road and Strand Road, opposite Rajakatra, on Sunday morning. The sergeant was rushed to Calcutta Medical Research Institute, where his condition was stated to be critical. The driver was arrested and the vehicle impounded by Burrabazar thana. 

 A seminar on ?Handicrafts in Bengal as an Income Generating Industry? will be organised at the Bengal National Chamber of Commerce and Industry auditorium from 10.30 am on July 2. Entrepreneurs at the seminar will explore possibilities in the handicrafts sector.

 The Indo-Vietnam Solidarity Committee will organise a function on Wednesday to felicitate Ngo Van Le, rector of the Vietnam National University, and Tran Binh Lam, head of international relations and research affairs. State parliamentary affairs minister Probodh Sinha will preside over the programme.

 A documentary film from Calcutta, Eshwar Mime Co, will be screened at the 26th Durban International Film Festival in South Africa, which will continue from June 15-26. The film was directed by stage and film personality Shyamanand Jalan.

 Usha Biswas, a 32-year-old housewife, was killed on the spot after the rickshaw-van she was travelling in was hit by a truck in Barasat, on the northern fringes of the city, on Saturday night. Police said Biswas was returning home in Ashokenagar. She was taken to the district hospital, where she was pronounced dead.

 Shanker Hela, 31, was arrested in Bantra, Howrah, on Sunday for allegedly being involved in a number of murder and extortion cases. A revolver and three bullets were seized from him. 

